# Kitchen Directory — Playwright E2E environment (copy to .env.e2e or export inline).
# Public-facing + form + unauthenticated-admin specs need NONE of these — they
# run against production out of the box. These only unlock the optional bits.

# Where the suite points. Defaults to the public prod alias.
# BASE_URL=https://kitchen-directory.vercel.app

# ── Authenticated admin flows (e2e/admin/authenticated/) ──
# Pick ONE method. Without either, admin-flow specs self-skip.
#
# Method A (preferred, non-destructive): service-role key → magic-link → session.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=ey...           # Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API
# E2E_ADMIN_EMAIL=rocco@theinfluenceagency.com   # must be on the ADMIN_EMAILS allow-list
#
# Method B (fallback): an admin user that has a password set.
# E2E_ADMIN_PASSWORD=...

# ── Valid-token verify-submission test (e2e/forms/verify-submission.spec.ts) ──
# Seed an `unverified` supplier_submissions row with a known verification_token,
# then put that token here. Otherwise the valid-token test self-skips.
# E2E_VERIFY_TOKEN=...
